ECON 4114 Industrial Organization & Competitive Strategy
Course Outline

Course Description, Objectives and Learning Outcomes

This course covers key aspects of an industry: market, rms, and regulator. Regarding the market
aspect, we cover market structures, market power, and sources of market power. Regarding rm behav-
iors, we cover topics on pricing, quality, branding, and asymmetric information. From the regulators
perspective, we cover welfare, regulation, and competition policy. Particular emphasis is placed on
game-theoretical models and their applications to real-world market interactions.
